#1. List and explain three 3 reasons why programmers write documentation. 
'they want people to see it'
'they will use the code later'
'they can go back to their code'

#2. In your own words, describe what a README.md document is.

'A read-me Document is a file that describes what is in your directory and about the creator.'

#3. Based on what you read, what are four (4) things that should be in a README document? 

' A brief but solid description, what part of the project you are on, how to install, and requirements needed.'

#4. Name and describe three (3) reasons why programmers write commit messages when using GitHub.

'to describe what changes were made, where the changes are, and what happened so the viewer can know what to look at.'

#5. Describe three things (3) negative outcomes that could happen if a programmer has bad or no documentation.

'The viewer may not know where to look, they may be misled on whats going on, and may not know how to install if they like it.'
